# Iter 1 тАФ fix email validation regex (security alert #3)

## Work done
- Added `email.length > 254` guard in `isValidEmail` before regex
- Rewrote regex from `/^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/` to `/^[^\s@]+@[^\s@.]+(?:\.[^\s@.]+)+$/`
  - Old regex: domain part used `[^\s@]+` which allows dots freely тЖТ accepts `a@b..c`, `a@.b.c`
  - New regex: domain uses `[^\s@.]+` (no dots) with explicit `(?:\.[^\s@.]+)+` тАФ requires at least one dot-separated label

## Verification (manual)
- Valid: `user@example.com` тЬУ, `a+b@sub.domain.io` тЬУ
- Invalid: `notanemail` тЬЧ, `@no-local.com` тЬЧ, `no-domain@` тЬЧ, `spaces @here.com` тЬЧ
- Invalid (previously passing): `a@b..c` тЬЧ, `a@.b.c` тЬЧ
- Over 254 chars тЬЧ
